Global Chicory Flour Market Insights
Chicory Flour Market size was valued at USD 1.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.0 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Chicory Flour Market Overview
The global Chicory Flour Market is projected to reach a value of USD 7.2 billion by 2028, expanding at a CAGR of 6.5% during the forecast period. The increasing demand for gluten-free and plant-based ingredients, along with growing health consciousness among consumers, is driving the market. Chicory flour is gaining popularity in food products such as bakery items, beverages, and snacks due to its nutritional benefits, including being a rich source of inulin and fiber. The market's growth is further supported by the rising adoption of chicory as a natural substitute for wheat flour in gluten-free products.

